-- Vietnam lender BIDV stocks rise 4 pct on domestic debut
-- By Ho Binh Minh
-- Thu Jan 23, 2014 09:33PM EST
-- None



HANOI, Jan 24 (Reuters) - Shares of Vietnam's second-largest lender BIDV <BID.HM> rose 4.3 percent to 19,500 dong ($0.9) each after its opening on the Ho Chi Minh Stock Exchange <.VNI> on Friday in the country's largest stock debut.

Shares of the Hanoi-based lender rose from a starting price of 18,700 dong each before reaching 19,500 dong at 0223 GMT. The VN Index also advanced 0.3 percent to 556.06 points.